    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">02</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Historical Context</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Early Usage of 'Texican' in Historical Records</h2><ul><li>Appears in documents from early 1800s Texas</li><li>Used by settlers of Mexican descent to assert identity</li><li>Reflects political and cultural shifts in Texas history</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">Historical documents from the early 19th century show 'Texican' used by Mexican-descended settlers to express their unique identity amid changing political landscapes, including Spanish, Mexican, and Texan governance. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s2\">[2]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> A letter from a Texican settler during the 1820s might emphasize loyalty to Mexican heritage while living in Texas territory.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Analyze how the term 'Texican' in historical documents signals cultural identity and political allegiance.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Ignoring the political implications of identity terms in historical texts.</p></div></div>",
