    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">08</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Identity Complexity</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Divided Loyalties of the Texicans</h2><ul><li>Texicans faced conflicting loyalties during Texas Revolution</li><li>Some supported Mexican government, others the Texan cause</li><li>Identity shaped by cultural ties and political pressures</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">During the Texas Revolution, Texicans experienced divided loyalties, torn between allegiance to Mexico and emerging Texan independence, reflecting complex identity dynamics. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s2\">[2]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> A Texican family might have members fighting on opposite sides of the conflict due to differing political beliefs.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Analyze how cultural identity influenced political loyalties among Texicans.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Assuming all Texicans uniformly supported one side in the revolution.</p></div></div>",
