    "num": "09",
    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">09</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Terminology in Context</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">How 'Texican' Reflects Cultural Blending</h2><ul><li>Term embodies fusion of Mexican and Texan identities</li><li>Represents borderland cultural hybridity</li><li>Highlights fluidity of identity in contested territories</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">'Texican' captures the cultural blending characteristic of Texas as a borderland, where Mexican and Anglo-American influences merged and identities evolved. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s2\">[2]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> Texican music and cuisine blend Mexican traditions with Texan frontier elements.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Identify examples of cultural blending that the term 'Texican' might represent.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Viewing cultural identities as fixed rather than fluid and evolving.</p></div><div id=\"quiz-slide9\" class=\"quizbox popquiz anim\" data-quiz=\"[{&quot;type&quot;:&quot;mc&quot;,&quot;level&quot;:2,&quot;q&quot;:&quot;Which of the following best distinguishes a &#39;Texican&#39; from a &#39;Texan&#39;?&quot;,&quot;options&quot;:[&quot;Texicans had Spanish and Mexican cultural roots, while Texans generally refers to all residents of Texas including Anglo settlers.&quot;,&quot;Texicans were only Anglo settlers, while Texans were native Mexicans.&quot;,&quot;Texicans were settlers after Texas became a U.S. state, Texans lived before statehood.&quot;,&quot;There is no difference; both terms mean the same.&quot;],&quot;answer&quot;:0,&quot;why&quot;:&quot;The term &#39;Texican&#39; specifically refers to early settlers with Spanish and Mexican heritage, while &#39;Texan&#39; is a broader term for all Texas residents.&quot;},{&quot;type&quot;:&quot;sa&quot;,&quot;level&quot;:3,&quot;q&quot;:&quot;Describe the political and military roles of the Texicans during the Texas Revolution and explain how their cultural background influenced their loyalties.&quot;,&quot;rubric&quot;:&quot;Response should identify Texicans&#39; participation in the Texas Revolution, mention their divided loyalties between Mexican and Texan causes, and explain how their Spanish-Mexican heritage and cultural blending influenced these positions.&quot;,&quot;sample&quot;:&quot;Texicans played complex roles in the Texas Revolution, with some supporting Mexican rule due to cultural ties, while others sided with Anglo settlers seeking independence. Their Spanish and Mexican heritage created divided loyalties that influenced their political and military actions.&quot;,&quot;accept&quot;:[&quot;Texicans had divided loyalties during the Texas Revolution influenced by their Spanish and Mexican cultural background, participating on both sides.&quot;,&quot;Their cultural heritage led some Texicans to support Mexico, while others joined the independence movement, reflecting complex political roles.&quot;]}]\" data-pop=\"1\"></div></div>",
