    "num": "16",
    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">16</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Geographic Impact</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">How Geography Shaped Texican Economic Activities</h2><ul><li>Fertile plains supported crop cultivation such as corn and cotton</li><li>Rivers enabled trade and transportation of goods</li><li>Open ranges facilitated large-scale cattle ranching</li><li>Geographic diversity required adaptive farming and ranching techniques</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">The varied geography of Texas influenced the Texicans' economic pursuits, requiring them to adapt their agricultural and ranching practices to local conditions. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s4\">[4]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s7\">[7]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> In coastal plains, Texicans grew cotton for export, while in drier interior regions, cattle ranching was more viable.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Match different Texican economic activities to their geographic settings and justify your choices.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Assuming uniform economic activities across all Texican settlements regardless of geography.</p></div></div>",
