    "eyebrow": "Settlement Challenges",
    "num": "18",
    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">18</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Settlement Challenges</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Environmental and Social Challenges Faced by Texicans</h2><ul><li>Frequent droughts and floods impacted agriculture and livestock</li><li>Conflicts with Native American groups affected settlement security</li><li>Isolation of rural settlements complicated trade and communication</li><li>Balancing traditional practices with new settlers' influences created social tensions</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">Texicans faced multiple challenges including environmental hardships, security threats, and social tensions arising from cultural interactions and geographic isolation. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s4\">[4]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s7\">[7]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> A drought could devastate crops and cattle, forcing Texicans to adapt their farming cycles or migrate temporarily.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Consider how Texicans might have addressed these challenges to sustain their communities.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Underestimating the impact of environmental and social challenges on Texican settlement stability.</p></div></div>",
