    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">19</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Cultural Practices</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Daily Life and Traditions of the Texicans</h2><ul><li>Family and religion were central to Texican daily routines</li><li>Festivals and communal gatherings reinforced social bonds</li><li>Traditional crafts such as weaving and leatherwork were common</li><li>Music and dance reflected a blend of Spanish and indigenous influences</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">Texican daily life was rich with cultural traditions that combined family, faith, and artistic expression, fostering a strong community identity. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s4\">[4]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s7\">[7]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> A Texican fiesta might include traditional music, dancing, and shared meals, celebrating religious or seasonal events.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Describe how cultural practices helped maintain Texican identity amid changing political landscapes.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Ignoring the role of cultural traditions in sustaining community cohesion.</p></div></div>",
