    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">23</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Critical Thinking</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Evaluating Sources on Texican Settlement and Lifestyle</h2><ul><li>Primary sources on Texican settlements are limited and often generalized</li><li>Secondary sources provide geographic and demographic context but lack detailed lifestyle descriptions</li><li>Cross-referencing multiple sources is necessary to build a fuller picture</li><li>Recognize potential biases and gaps in historical records</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">Understanding Texican settlement and lifestyle requires critical evaluation of available sources, acknowledging their limitations and synthesizing evidence carefully. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s4\">[4]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s7\">[7]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> Maps and demographic data outline settlement areas, but personal letters or mission records are needed to understand daily life nuances.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Identify what types of sources would best fill gaps in knowledge about Texican lifestyle and why.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Accepting incomplete or biased sources at face value without critical analysis.</p></div></div>",
