    "eyebrow": "Cultural Influences",
    "num": "25",
    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">25</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Cultural Influences</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Spanish Colonial Legacy in Texican Culture</h2><ul><li>Spanish colonial rule shaped early Texican social structures and traditions</li><li>Language, religion (Catholicism), and legal systems reflected Spanish origins</li><li>Land grant policies influenced settlement and land use patterns</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">The Texicans inherited many cultural elements from Spanish colonial governance, including language, religion, and legal traditions. These influences persisted even as political control shifted. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s2\">[2]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s6\">[6]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> Many Texican families practiced Catholicism and celebrated Spanish religious festivals, maintaining cultural continuity despite political changes.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Identify specific Spanish cultural elements that might still be visible in Texican communities today.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Assuming Texican culture was purely Anglo-American without recognizing deep Spanish roots.</p></div></div>",
