    "id": "slide26",
    "eyebrow": "Cultural Blending",
    "num": "26",
    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">26</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Cultural Blending</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Mexican Governance and Texican Adaptation</h2><ul><li>Mexican independence introduced new political and cultural dynamics</li><li>Texicans adapted Spanish traditions under Mexican law and governance</li><li>Mexican policies encouraged Anglo-American immigration, complicating identity</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">After Mexico gained independence, Texicans navigated a new political landscape that blended Spanish colonial legacies with Mexican national identity, while also facing increasing Anglo-American influence. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s2\">[2]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s6\">[6]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s7\">[7]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> Texicans participated in Mexican political institutions but also welcomed Anglo settlers, leading to cultural hybridity and tensions.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Discuss how Mexican governance might have altered Texican cultural practices or loyalties.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Viewing Mexican rule as a simple continuation of Spanish control without recognizing its distinct impact.</p></div></div>",
