    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">28</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Identity Conflicts</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Loyalty and Identity: Divided Allegiances of the Texicans</h2><ul><li>Texicans faced conflicting loyalties to Spain, Mexico, and Anglo settlers</li><li>Political upheavals intensified identity struggles</li><li>These divided loyalties influenced Texican participation in Texas Revolution</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">The Texicans' cultural blending created complex loyalties that were tested during political transitions, especially during the Texas Revolution. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s2\">[2]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s6\">[6]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s7\">[7]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> Some Texicans supported Mexican rule while others allied with Anglo settlers seeking independence.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Analyze how cultural identity influenced Texican political choices during the revolution.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Oversimplifying Texican loyalties as uniformly pro-Anglo or pro-Mexican.</p></div></div>",
