    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">32</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Cultural Challenges</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Challenges to Texican Identity from Anglo Expansion</h2><ul><li>Anglo immigration increased pressure on land and resources</li><li>Legal and political systems shifted toward Anglo-American models</li><li>Texicans faced marginalization and cultural erosion risks</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">The growing Anglo presence challenged Texican cultural dominance and created pressures to assimilate or resist. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s2\">[2]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s6\">[6]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s7\">[7]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> Texican landowners sometimes lost property due to changing legal frameworks favoring Anglo settlers.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Analyze how Anglo expansion threatened Texican cultural and economic stability.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Assuming Texican culture was unaffected by Anglo demographic changes.</p></div></div>",
