    "eyebrow": "Texicans in the Texas Revolution",
    "num": "37",
    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">37</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Texicans in the Texas Revolution</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Political Roles of Texicans During the Revolution</h2><ul><li>Texicans held diverse political views during the Texas Revolution</li><li>Some supported Mexican governance, others favored independence</li><li>Texicans participated in local councils and provisional governments</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">Texicans were politically active during the Texas Revolution, with loyalties divided between Mexican rule and the push for Texan independence. Their involvement in local governance reflected these tensions and shaped revolutionary politics. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s2\">[2]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s7\">[7]</sup> <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s8\">[8]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> Texican leaders like José Antonio Navarro advocated for Texan rights within Mexico before supporting independence.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Analyze how Texican political participation influenced the direction of the Texas Revolution.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Assuming all Texicans uniformly supported independence without recognizing internal divisions.</p></div></div>",
