    "eyebrow": "Newspaper Analysis",
    "num": "53",
    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">53</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Newspaper Analysis</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Using Newspapers to Understand Texican Public Opinion</h2><ul><li>Newspapers capture debates, announcements, and political views</li><li>They reflect the diversity of opinions among Texicans</li><li>Editorial bias and censorship must be considered</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">Newspapers from the Texican era provide a window into public discourse and political tensions. Analyzing articles and editorials reveals how Texicans expressed identity and responded to events. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s17\">[17]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> An editorial supporting Texas independence shows one faction’s perspective during the revolution.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> Analyze a newspaper excerpt to identify the author’s stance and intended audience.</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Assuming newspapers represent unanimous public opinion without recognizing editorial slant.</p></div></div>",
