    "eyebrow": "Practice with a Letter Excerpt",
    "num": "54",
    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">54</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Practice with a Letter Excerpt</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Interpreting a Texican Letter: Step-by-Step</h2><ul><li>Read the excerpt carefully for tone and content</li><li>Identify expressions of identity or political views</li><li>Consider the historical context of the letter’s date</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">Applying source analysis skills to a real Texican letter excerpt helps learners practice interpreting personal perspectives and historical context. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s15\">[15]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> A letter dated 1835 expresses concern over Mexican policies and hints at support for Texas independence.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> What does this letter reveal about the writer’s loyalties and cultural identity? What questions remain?</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Ignoring the date or historical events surrounding the letter’s creation.</p></div></div>",
