    "num": "55",
    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">55</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Practice with a Legal Document</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Decoding a Texican Land Grant</h2><ul><li>Identify key legal terms and their meanings</li><li>Note the parties involved and their roles</li><li>Consider how the document reflects Texican settlement patterns</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">Analyzing a land grant helps learners understand how Texicans secured property and navigated Mexican legal systems. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s16\">[16]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> A land grant issued by Mexican authorities to a Texican settler formalizes ownership and obligations.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> What does this document reveal about Texican-Mexican relations and social status?</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Overlooking the significance of legal formalities or assuming uniform treatment of settlers.</p></div></div>",
