    "num": "56",
    "deck": "<div class=\"wrap\"><div class=\"eyebrow anim\"><span class=\"num\">56</span><span class=\"bar\"></span>Practice with a Newspaper Excerpt</div><h2 class=\"head anim\">Evaluating a Texican Newspaper Editorial</h2><ul><li>Identify the author’s main argument and tone</li><li>Look for persuasive language or appeals</li><li>Consider the intended audience and political context</li></ul><p class=\"lede anim\">Analyzing a newspaper editorial reveals how Texicans publicly debated identity and political issues during the revolution. <sup class=\"cite\" data-src=\"s17\">[17]</sup></p><div class=\"lesson-detail anim\"><p><strong>Example:</strong> An editorial advocating for Texas independence uses emotive language to rally support.</p><p><strong>Practice:</strong> What biases or assumptions are present? How might different Texican groups respond?</p><p><strong>Watch for:</strong> Taking editorial opinions as factual without recognizing persuasive intent.</p></div></div>",
